Syringomyelia as a postoperative sequela of the resection of a chordoma of the clivus: case report.
 Syringomyelia has been described frequently in association with various abnormalities of the skull base but rarely with tumors of the skull base.
 Syringomyelia as a postoperative sequela of surgery of the skull base has not been reported.
 The authors describe a case of cervical syringomyelia developing after the partial resection of a chordoma and combined conventional and proton beam irradiation.
 The possible mechanisms causing this abnormality are discussed.
